TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {44184=Copyright © 2015, 26786= Thank you for participating in the David Rummage Memorial Benefit on Friday, July 19, 2013!  The staff and volunteers would like to thank you for your kindness, support, and/or donation(s) during the planning of this event. , 27852= The Post Office would have made over 400,000 dollars in 2012, but for a death stroke bill passed in December 2006 which mandated that within 10 years the Post Office had to pony up 75 years in advance for all the healthcare benefits of all the postal retirees. This burden cost the Post Office over 6 billion dollars a year. That kind of burden would kill any department of business, especially when it is regulated by a postal commission.}
